## 4. State Machine & Flow Control

> 목적: Happy Path 외의 모든 상태를 명시적으로 정의

### 4.1 Core State Machines

```
[Entity: Order]
States: DRAFT → PENDING_PAYMENT → PAID → SHIPPING → DELIVERED → COMPLETED
                                    ↘ CANCELLED (from DRAFT, PENDING_PAYMENT)
                                    ↘ REFUND_REQUESTED → REFUNDED (from PAID, DELIVERED)

Transition Rules:
- DRAFT → PENDING_PAYMENT: requires all mandatory fields filled
- PENDING_PAYMENT → PAID: payment gateway webhook confirmation
- PAID → CANCELLED: triggers refund side-effect
- Any → CANCELLED: only within 24h of creation

Side Effects:
- PAID: emit OrderPaid event, decrement inventory
- SHIPPED: send notification email
- REFUNDED: increment inventory, emit RefundProcessed event
```

### 4.2 Frontend Async State Pattern

```typescript
type AsyncState<T> =
  | { status: 'IDLE' }
  | { status: 'LOADING' }
  | { status: 'SUCCESS'; data: T }
  | { status: 'ERROR'; error: AppError; retryCount: number }
```

**Retry & Timeout Policy**:
| Parameter            | Value             |
|----------------------|-------------------|
| Max Retries          | 3 (📌 DEFAULT)    |
| Retry Strategy       | Exponential Backoff (📌 DEFAULT) |
| Base Delay           | 1000ms            |
| Request Timeout      | 5000ms (📌 DEFAULT)|
| Circuit Breaker      | Yes / No          |

